22 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 6-17-429(b) and (c), concerning
23 requirements for certain individuals to have proficient knowledge and skills
24 to teach reading and obtain certain professional development under the Right
25 to Read Act, are amended to read as follows:
26 (b)(1)(A) No later than 2023, the The following shall have proficient
27 knowledge and skills to teach reading consistent with the best practices of
28 scientific reading instruction:
29 (i) A person who completes a state-approved educator
30 preparation program; and
31 (ii) A person seeking teacher licensure by
32 reciprocity or by adding an endorsement.
33 (B) No later than 2023, a A person who completes a state-
34 approved educator preparation program other than a teacher of elementary
35 education program shall demonstrate an awareness of the best practices of
36 scientific reading instruction.
