1 (2) Beginning no later than the 2022-2023 school year, each Each
2 state-approved educator preparation program shall post on its website
3 information describing its program to prepare teachers to teach reading using
4 scientific reading instruction aligned with but not limited to the content
5 measured by the stand-alone reading assessment adopted by the State Board of
6 Education under § 6-17-402.
7 (c)(1) Beginning with the 2018-2019 school year, a Each public school
8 district and an open-enrollment public charter school shall provide the
9 following professional development in scientific reading instruction:
10 (A) For teachers licensed at the elementary level in
11 kindergarten through grade six (K-6), teachers with a special education
12 license in kindergarten through grade twelve (K-12), and teachers licensed as
13 reading specialists in kindergarten through grade twelve (K-12), professional
14 development for one (1) of the prescribed pathways to obtaining a proficiency
15 credential in knowledge and practices in scientific reading instruction; and
16 (B) For teachers licensed at a level other than the
17 elementary level in kindergarten through grade six (K-6), teachers with a
18 special education license in kindergarten through grade twelve (K-12), and
19 teachers licensed as reading specialists in kindergarten through grade twelve
20 (K-12), professional development for one (1) of the prescribed pathways to
21 obtaining an awareness credential in knowledge and practices in scientific
22 reading instruction.
23 (2) Beginning with the 2020-2021 school year, a Each public
24 school or open-enrollment public charter school that does not provide the
25 professional development under subdivision (c)(1) of this section shall:
26 (A) Be placed in probationary status; and
27 (B) Provide notice to parents that the public school
28 district has not met the requirements of this section.
