9 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 6-17-429(f)-(h), concerning resources,
10 curriculum programs, and professional development requirements under the
11 Right to Read Act, are amended to read as follows:
12 (f) By the beginning of the 2020-2021 school year, the The division
13 shall identify and create an approved list of materials, resources, and
14 curriculum programs for public school districts and open-enrollment public
15 charter schools that are supported by the science of reading and based on
16 instruction that is explicit, systematic, cumulative, and diagnostic,
17 including without limitation:
18 (1) Dyslexia programs that are evidence-based and:
19 (A) Aligned to structured literacy; or
20 (B) Grounded in the Orton-Gillingham methodology;
21 (2) Evidence-based reading intervention programs; and
22 (3) Evidence-based reading programs that are grounded in the
23 science of reading.
24 (g)(1) By the beginning of the 2021-2022 school year, any A public
25 school district and open-enrollment public charter school purchasing that
26 purchases a curriculum program shall choose a curriculum program from the
27 division's approved list of curriculum programs created under subsection (f)
28 of this section.
29 (2) A public school district or open-enrollment public charter
30 school that chooses to purchase a curriculum program that is not from the
31 division's approved list of curriculum programs shall submit the following to
32 the division for approval of the alternative curriculum program:
33 (A) A rationale for choosing the alternative curriculum
34 program; and
35 (B) Evidence-based research regarding the alternative
36 curriculum program.
